▲广州街头，戴着口罩的行人。
Guangzhou streets, wearing masks of pedestrians.
（麦圈/图）全文共2050字，阅读大约需要5分钟。
The full text is 2050 words and will take about 5 minutes to read.
一场突如其来的疫情，给中国人带来近十年来最长的一个春节假期。
A sudden epidemic has brought the Chinese the longest Spring Festival in nearly a decade.
随着2月10日的复工，城市正逐渐恢复往日的样貌。
With the resumption of work on February 10, the city is gradually returning to its former shape.
本文首发于南方周末 未经授权 不得转载文 | 南方周末记者 刘诗洋责任编辑 | 顾策2020年2月10日，疫情笼罩的漫长假期终于结束，但城市的复苏似乎仍需等待。
This article began at Southern Weekend without authorization to reproduce & # 160; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45;
早在2020年1月27日，国务院就宣布延长春节假期，随后各地政府逐步跟进，大部分省市将复工时间定在了2月10日。
As early as January 27, 2020, the State Council announced the extension of the Spring Festival holiday, followed by local governments, most provinces and municipalities scheduled the resumption of work for February 10.
北京最热闹的三里屯，大部分店家都关门歇业。
Most shops in Sanlitun, Beijing's busiest town, have closed their doors.
（刘诗洋/图）这一天上午8点，早高峰时段，首都北京的交通广播罕见地通报全城畅通。
(Liu Shiyang / Picture) This day at 8: 00 a.m., early rush hour, the capital Beijing traffic radio rarely informs the whole city open.
国贸东三环桥，司机们踩油门的右脚多少会有点不适应——这个限速80km的路口平时连一半速度都达不到，现在稍不注意就会超速。
At the East Triple Ring Bridge, drivers who pedal on the gas pedal's right foot are a bit out of whack -- the 80-km intersection doesn't reach half its normal speed, and can overspeed if you don't watch it.
东三环桥下的北京国贸CBD，仍在疫情中沉睡。
DongSanhuan Bridge under the Beijing International Trade Center CBD, is still sleeping in the epidemic.
因为没有车流，路口的红灯显得时间过长。
Because there was no traffic, the red light at the intersection seemed too long.
人流最密集的大北窑公交站和国贸地铁人烟稀少。
The most densely populated bus station and the International Trade Center Metro are sparsely populated.
写字楼一改往日的热闹，仅有的几个白领在前台测量体温后，不想多停留一分钟。
Office building a lively past, only a few white-collar workers in front of the temperature measurement, do not want to stay for one more minute.
上午九点，空荡无人的北京国贸CBD光华路。
9: 00 a.m., empty Beijing International Trade Center CBD Guanghua Road.
（刘诗洋/图）在疫情还未褪去之时，不少人对回公司上班仍有些担心。
While the epidemic is still unfolding, many people are still worried about returning to work.
上午10点，在上海一家公司做会计的李冉，戴上两层口罩出门去上班，包里还装着两个备用。
Li Ran, an accountant at a Shanghai-based company, is wearing a two-storey mask to work with two spare parts in his bag.
她最担心的是中午吃饭的问题，她不敢吃外卖，也不想在公开场合摘下口罩那么长时间。
Her biggest worry was lunchtime meals, which she did not dare to eat or take off in public for as long as she needed.
她母亲出门前还告诉她，如果来上班的人多，下午就请假回家。
Her mother also told her that if more people came to work, she would take the afternoon off to go home.
上海经信委副主任张英在2月10日的新闻发布会上表示，根据他们的抽样调查，有80%的制造业企业希望复工，这部分企业的复工率已经到达70%。
Zhang Ying, deputy director of the Shanghai Economic and Communications Commission, said at a news conference on Feb. 10 that, according to their sample, 80 percent of manufacturing enterprises want to return to work, and the rate of return to work in those enterprises has reached 70 percent.
另外，软件和信息服务业，目前仍以居家办公为主，但也有80%以上开始复工。
In addition, the software and information services industry is still largely home-based, but more than 80 per cent have begun to return to work.
一些明星企业复工的影响力甚至波及海外。
The impact of the resumption of some star companies has even spread overseas.
特斯拉上海工厂的首日复工，令其股票在盘前上涨5.47%。
Tesla's Shanghai plant resumed work on its first day, sending its shares up 5.47 per cent ahead of the day.
这家备受瞩目的新能源车企，此前因推出低价版的国产Model3而获得中国消费者的广泛关注，但受疫情影响，他们表示原定2月初的交付会暂缓。
The high-profile new-energy car maker, which has been widely watched by Chinese consumers after launching a low-priced version of its home-made Model 3, has said deliveries originally scheduled for early February will be put on hold because of the outbreak.
而在崇尚美食、气候温和的广州，最令人瞩目的是消费和服务行业的苏醒——它们原本是受疫情影响最大的行业。
The most remarkable of Guangzhou's culinary and temperate climate is the revival of consumer and service sectors, which were originally the most affected by the epidemic.
《南方都市报》记者在2月10日的报道中称，广州一些商场内店铺的开张率已达到八九成。
The Southern Metropolis Daily reported on February 10 that the opening rate of shops in some shopping malls in Guangzhou had reached 89 percent.
广州一些理发店已经开张。
Some barber shops in Guangzhou have opened.
（麦圈/图）一位经营民宿酒店的老板告诉南方周末记者，他认识的很多餐饮业老板都在筹划开工，尽管目前一些地方还不允许开工。
The owner of a residential hotel told Southern Weekend that many restaurant owners he knew were planning to start work, although some were not allowed to do so at the moment.
尽管疫情要求人们尽量少接触，但这天上午，他还是遵循传统，给员工派发了红包。
Though the outbreak required minimal contact, he followed tradition by giving out red packets to employees that morning.
广州地铁里，人们穿着厚厚的防护衣。
People wear thick protective clothing in Guangzhou Metro.
（麦圈/图）广州地铁里，人们穿着厚厚的防护衣。
In the Guangzhou Metro, people wear thick protective clothing.
（麦圈/图）与繁忙的一线城市相比，全国其他地方的复工情况仍要让位于疫情管控。
The return to work in the rest of the country still has to give way to disease control compared to the busy frontline cities.
在浙江温州，所有企业都不得在2月17日24时前复工，江西景德镇公布的复工日期则延缓到24号。
In Wenzhou, Zhejiang, all enterprises are not allowed to resume work before 2400 hours February 17, Jiangxi Jingdezhen announced the resumption of work date postponed to 24.
而在郑州，政府要求企业要按照员工结构分别复工：本地员工为主的，不早于2月10日复工，疫区员工少的，可以在17号复工。
In Zhengzhou, the government required enterprises to resume work according to their employee structure: those with local employees mainly returning to work no earlier than February 10, and those with fewer employees in affected areas may resume work on February 17.
除此之外的其他企业，都要求2月24日复工。
Other businesses, among others, are expected to resume work on February 24.
此外，还有一些城市则实行核准制，杭州市在2月10日之前共接到近3万家企业的复工申请，但只有162家被核准通过。
In other cities, approvals were given, and by February 10 Hangzhou had received applications from nearly 30,000 companies to resume work, but only 162 had been approved.
同样需要核准的还有深圳，一位从事手机配件生产的深圳公司老板告诉南方周末记者，他早在上周就递交了复工资料，但目前还没有接到许可。
Also in need of approval is Shenzhen, a Shenzhen company engaged in the production of mobile phone accessories owner told Southern Weekend that he had submitted information last week, but so far has not received permission.
深圳目前批准复工的主要是大中型企业，万科集团选在了2月10日复工，而华为则早于2月3日就已经部分复工。
Shenzhen approved the resumption of work is mainly large and medium-sized enterprises, Vanke Group selected February 10 to resume work, Huawei as early as February 3 has been part of the resumption of work.
也许是因为SARS时期的恐慌。
Perhaps because of the SARS panic.
在北京工作的人似乎对复工更为保守，从依旧冷清的北京国贸再向西北30公里，平日里码农遍地的中关村软件园也还在沉睡。
People working in Beijing seem to be more conservative about returning to work, from the still-deserted Beijing International Trade Center to the northwest 30 kilometers northwest, where the usual Zhongguancun software park is still sleeping.
2月10日中午12点，往日车流不息的腾讯总部门前只有几个保安驻守，旁边的网易、新浪、联想也是一片冷清。
Feb. 10 noon, the old traffic flow Tencent headquarters in front of only a few security guards, next to Netease, Sina, Lenovo is also a cold.
上午11点，网易和百度大楼门前一个人都没有。
At 11 a.m., Netease and Baidu building in front of a person is not.
（刘诗洋/图）中关村软件园里以往最热闹的咖啡店和吸烟处，只有寥寥数人。
There are only a few people in Zhongguancun Software Park, the busiest coffee shop and smoking section in the past.
在这片区域工作三年，换了四家公司的程序员于然告诉南方周末记者，他的工作完全可以在家里完成，在疫情彻底过去之前，他不会去上班。
After three years in the area, programmers at four different companies told Southern Weekend that his job could be done at home and he would not go to work until the epidemic was completely over.
事实上，相比于中小企业，互联网巨头们的复工计划已算相当人性化。
In fact, the Internet giants "plans to get back to work are quite humane compared to those of small and medium-sized enterprises.
百度、搜狐、美团等多家大型互联网公司的员工告诉南方周末记者，他们本周仍以网络办公为主，返岗日期都推迟到17号以后，而腾讯和今日头条，则直接把假期延长到了2月24号。
Employees at several big internet companies, including Baidu, Sohu and USM, told Southern Weekend that they still focus on networking this week, postponing their return to work beyond February 17, while Tencent and headlines today have extended their holidays directly to Feb. 24.
广州街头，防疫人员拦住车辆测量体温。
Guang Zhou street, epidemic prevention personnel stopped the vehicle to take temperature.
（麦圈/图）据58同城招聘近期发布的《2020年疫情对企业复工与招聘影响调研报告》显示，47%的企业将在2月10日复工。
According to a recently released report on the impact of the 2020 epidemic on the resumption of work and recruitment, 47 percent of businesses will return to work on February 10.
15%的企业在2月10日以后复工，仍有27%的企业（截至2月5日统计）还未确定复工时间。
Fifteen per cent of enterprises returned to work after 10 February, and 27 per cent (as at 5 February) had not set a time limit for resuming work.
广州街头，随处可见检测体温的工作台。
Temperature screening stations are common on the streets of Guangzhou.
（麦圈/图）在采取延时复工的企业中，55%企业采取在家办公方式；32%企业休假，有工作响应即可；13%的企业正常休假。
Wheat Circle / Diagram 55 per cent of enterprises that have resumed work on a time-delayed basis take home-based work, 32 per cent are on leave with a work response, and 13 per cent are on regular leave.
这表明，绝大部分企业采取了线上灵活办公方式，而根据58同城招聘调研数据显示，在家办公的企业中，51%属于IT、通信、电子及互联网行业。
This suggests that the vast majority of businesses are flexible online, while 51 per cent of home-based businesses are in the IT, communications, electronics and Internet industries, according to 58 homemade recruitment surveys.
一场突如其来的疫情，给中国人带来近十年来最长的一个春节假期。
A sudden epidemic has brought the Chinese the longest Spring Festival in nearly a decade.
随着2月10日的复工，城市正逐渐恢复往日的样貌。
With the resumption of work on February 10, the city is gradually returning to its former shape.
夜里九点，中央电视台记者以直播的形式，乘车环绕北京，镜头再次掠过国贸CBD，在灯光的装点下，它看起来稍微恢复了一点往日的繁华。
9: 00 pm, CCTV reporters in the form of a live ride around Beijing, the camera again skimmed over the ITC CBD, decorated with lights, it seems to restore a bit of the former prosperity.
在没有疫情的时候，北京CBD这片不足10平方公里的区域，在2018年创造了高达3163亿的GDP。
In the absence of the epidemic, Beijing's CBD, an area of less than 10 square kilometers, generated $316.3 billion in GDP in 2018.
因为数以万计的企业、总部机构入驻，这里是北京人流最密集的区域。
Because tens of thousands of enterprises, headquarters agencies are stationed here in Beijing is the most densely populated area.
同样在此办公的仲量联行就曾做过一次统计，平均每天有超过40万人在此办公。
Also working here in the middle of the Union has done a statistical, an average of more than 400,000 people work here every day.
然而和全国许多地方一样，它的运行方式正在发生着极大的变化。
However, as in many parts of the country, the way it works is changing dramatically.
广州地铁里，上班的人群接受体温检测。
People going to work in Guangzhou Metro undergo a temperature test.
（麦圈/图）征集《南方周末》现向所有身处新冠肺炎一线的读者公开征集新闻线索。
Southern Weekend is now collecting news leads from all readers who are on the front line of the new crown pneumonia.
我们欢迎武汉及周边城市医患联系记者，提供防疫前线的一手资讯，讲述您的新春疫情见闻。
We welcome Wuhan and surrounding city doctors and patients contact reporters, provide a first-hand epidemic prevention information, to tell you about the New Year.
若您不在武汉，但您身处之所也有与疫情相关的重要新闻线索，亦欢迎您与我们分享。
If you are not in Wuhan, but you are in a place where you also have important news clues related to the epidemic, you are welcome to share with us.
疫情仍在蔓延，南方周末将执笔记录每位国人在疫情面前的希望与困境，与广大读者共同面对疫情。
The epidemic is still spreading. Southern Weekend will write about the hopes and difficulties of every Chinese people in the face of the epidemic and face the epidemic together with readers.
祝愿所有读者朋友们，新春平安。
Wish all readers a safe New Year.
